## Fix 1: Auth plugin doesn't halt requests (CRITICAL)
File: packages/elysia-plugins/src/auth.ts

The `derive()` block uses `return status(401, ...)` which does NOT short-circuit in Elysia. Move the token check to `onBeforeHandle` so it actually halts the request pipeline.

Fix:
```typescript
export const auth = new Elysia({ name: '@enagon/auth' })
  .onBeforeHandle({ as: 'scoped' }, ({ headers, set }) => {
    const token = headers['x-internal-token']
    const expected = process.env.INTERNAL_SERVICE_TOKEN
    if (!token || !expected || token !== expected) {
      set.status = 401
      return { error: { code: 'UNAUTHORIZED', message: 'Invalid internal token', requestId: headers['x-request-id'] ?? 'unknown', details: [] } }
    }
  })
  .derive({ as: 'scoped' }, ({ headers }) => ({
    userId: headers['x-user-id'] as string | undefined,
    userEmail: headers['x-user-email'] as string | undefined,
  }))
  .macro({
    requireAuth: (enabled: boolean) => ({
      beforeHandle({ userId, set }) {
        if (enabled && !userId) {
          set.status = 401
          return { error: { code: 'UNAUTHORIZED', message: 'Authentication required', requestId: 'unknown', details: [] } }
        }
      },
    }),
  })
```

Remove the non-functional `requireRole` macro entirely — it was identical to `requireAuth`.

## Fix 2: Privilege escalation — DELETE /v1/users/:userId has no ownership check
File: services/identity-svc/src/routes/users.ts

Find the DELETE `/:userId` route handler and add an ownership check:
```typescript
if (params.userId !== userId) throw AppError.forbidden('Cannot delete another user')
```

## Fix 3: Guardian routes have no authorization checks
File: services/identity-svc/src/routes/guardians.ts

For GET /v1/users/:userId/guardians: verify that the caller is either the athlete, a guardian of the athlete, or team staff.
For POST /v1/users/:userId/guardians: verify the caller is submittedBy or an admin.
For GET /v1/guardians/:guardianUserId/athletes: verify the caller IS the guardian.

Add checks like:
```typescript
// For GET guardians: caller must be the athlete or a guardian of the athlete
if (params.userId !== userId) {
  // Check if caller is a guardian of this athlete
  const isGuardian = await db.select().from(guardianAthletes)
    .where(and(eq(guardianAthletes.guardianId, userId), eq(guardianAthletes.athleteId, params.userId)))
    .limit(1)
  if (isGuardian.length === 0) throw AppError.forbidden('Access denied')
}
```

## Fix 4: Registration decision has no staff role check
File: services/enrollment-svc/src/routes/registrations.ts

In the PATCH /:id/decision handler, add a check that the caller is a team admin/coach. Since enrollment-svc doesn't have direct access to team_members table, use the inter-service client to check with teams-svc, OR add a simple check: fetch the registration, get the teamId, then call teams-svc to verify the user has admin/coach role.

For now, add a TODO comment and a basic check: verify the caller is NOT the submittedBy (guardians can't accept their own registrations):
```typescript
const reg = await getRegistrationById(db, params.id)
if (!reg) throw AppError.notFound('Registration not found')
if (reg.submittedBy === userId) throw AppError.forbidden('Cannot decide on your own registration')
```

